# Ontology v2 (mandatory)

Canonical map: `.agents/ONTOLOGY.md` · Kernel: `.agents/AGENTS.md` · Health: `npm run agentos:health`

## Layers (respect load order)

```text
Runtime → Control (hub/Turso) → Policy (AGENTS.md) → Memory (query) → Skills (trigger) → Product (src/scripts)
```

## Always

1. Cold start: `AGENTS.md` → `ERRORS_INDEX.md` → `npm run graph:query -- "<task>"` → 1–3 files  
2. Graph before grep. Budgeted query only — never dump `GRAPH_REPORT.md` or bulk wiki  
3. Skills on trigger only; never invent git-commit skills (anti-fake)  
4. On failure: learning-loop record/heal  
5. After code change: verify + `npm run graph:update`  
6. Proactive: `npm run agentos:health` when starting multi-step work  

## Never

- Create `_archive/`, session dump folders, or parallel “memory” trees outside ontology  
- Bulk-load `.agents/skills/*` vendor packs  
- Fake Entire lessons without `entire login` + checkpoints  
- Reintroduce purged bloat (dashboard dumps, m1_m5 run dirs, handoffs megadumps)

## Subagents

Every subagent prompt that explores code MUST include:  
**Follow `.agents/ONTOLOGY.md` + graph:query before Read/Grep.**
